Will the United States still be fighting shadowy opponents in distant lands?
North Korea and Pakistan had no nuclear weapons, but the United States and Soviet Union together had more than 50,000.
The United States had more than 200,000 troops in Europe and hardly any in the Middle East.
You could smoke on airplanes, in restaurants, and inside most public buildings, but smoking pot anywhere in the United States could land you in jail.
There were only three television networks in the United States (plus public TV), and Saturday Night Live was fresh and funny.